1 Download the ISO https://cdimage.debian.org/cdimage/archive/11.11.0/ iso-cd debian 11.11 netinst iso
2 Flash the iso from cd dvd or cd
3 Setup Debian 11
4 When on Software Selection Deselect Debian Desktop Environment leave it standard system utilities
5 After Install run su - then apt install doas then nano /etc/doas.conf then permit persist username as root (Change username to your username)
6 Run doas apt update && doas apt upgrade -y
7 Run doas apt install links -y
  then links https://github.com/syslacklinux/Forsaken-Linux/ then click enter on Screenshot From 2026-07-17 13-56-15 
  Then after click enter change the name 623065669-de80debd-40f3-4822-8c91-d3403ed04c46 To forsaken-logo.png
  Then run doas mv /home/username/forsaken-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps (Change username to your username)
  Then doas cp /usr/share/pixmaps/forsaken-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/debian-logo.png
8 Run doas nano /etc/os-release then change
  
  PRETTY_NAME="Debian GNU/Linux 11 (bullseye)"
  NAME="Debian GNU/Linux"
  VERSION_ID="11"
  VERSION="11 (bullseye)"
  VERSION_CODENAME=bullseye
  ID=debian
  HOME_URL="https://www.debian.org/"
  SUPPORT_URL="https://www.debian.org/support"
  BUG_REPORT_URL="https://bugs.debian.org/"

  To

  PRETTY_NAME="Forsaken Linux 1 (eclipse)"
  NAME="Forsaken Linux"
  VERSION_ID="1"
  VERSION="1 (eclipse)"
  VERSION_CODENAME=eclipse
  ID=forsaken
  HOME_URL="https://github.com/syslacklinux/Forsaken-Linux"
  SUPPORT_URL="https://github.com/syslacklinux/Forsaken-Linux/discussions/1"
  BUG_REPORT_URL="https://github.com/syslacklinux/Forsaken-Linux/issues"
  LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/forsaken-logo.png

CTRL X Y ENTER and prevent from getting resetted by running doas apt-mark hold base-files

9 Run doas nano /etc/issue
  Then change Debian GNU/Linux 11 \n \l to Welcome to \s \r \m (\l)
CTRL X Y ENTER

10 Run doas rm /etc/issue.net
11 Run doas nano /etc/default/grub
   Then change GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR='lsb_release -i -s 2> /dev/null || echo Debian' to GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Forsaken Linux"
   On GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT Remove quiet so it will be GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT=""
CTRL X Y Enter then doas /usr/sbin/grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
12 run doas nano /etc/grub.d/10_linux then change OS=GNU/Linux to OS= on if [ "x${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR}" = "x" ] ; then
   CTRL X Y ENTER then doas /usr/sbin/grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
13 Run doas apt install bsdgames fortune
14 Run doas nano ~/.bashrc
   Then at very end add uname -r;fortune
15 run doas rm /etc/motd
16 Create a Forsaken origin file doas nano /etc/dpkg/origins/forsaken
   Add

   Vendor: Forsaken Linux
   Vendor-URL: https://github.com/syslacklinux/Forsaken-Linux
   Bugs: https://github.com/syslacklinux/Forsaken-Linux/issues

CTRL X Y ENTER Then doas ln -sf /etc/dpkg/origins/forsaken /etc/dpkg/origins/default
